  "texts": [
    "For instance, generative systems can propose candidate molecules optimized for sweetness or floral notes while satisfying toxicity and solubility constraints.",
    "This capability opens new possibilities for functional food formulation, personalized fragrances, and sustainable alternatives to rare natural compounds.",
    "Explainable AI (XAI) is increasingly vital in applications that require transparency (Sarkar et al. 2025), especially in health diagnostics, food safety, and consumer-facing tools.",
    "Beyond basic attribution methods, emerging approaches such as counterfactual reasoning, prototype learning, and knowledge distillation offer richer interpretability tailored to chemical and sensory data.",
    "XAI tools can help identify which substructures in a molecule contribute to specific taste or odor labels, or explain why a formulation is predicted to elicit a particular consumer response."
